This is a textbook case of **coverage-gaming** — every production method is called, achieving high coverage, but almost nothing meaningful is verified. Here's the severity-ranked audit:

---

## 🔴 Critical — Assert-Free Tests (coverage without verification)

These tests call production code but never assert outcomes. They only prove the code doesn't throw.

**1. `AddProduct_Works` (line 17)** — No assertion that the product was actually stored.
```csharp
// Fix: verify round-trip
_catalog.AddProduct(product);
var saved = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.AreEqual("Widget", saved?.Name);
Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, saved?.Price);
```

**2. `UpdatePrice_Works` (line 32)** — Calls `UpdatePrice` but never checks the new price.
```csharp
// Fix: assert the mutation
_catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);
Assert.AreEqual(14.99m, _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001")?.Price);
```

**3. `RemoveProduct_Works` (line 39)** — Never verifies the product is gone.
```csharp
// Fix: assert deletion
_catalog.RemoveProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.IsNull(_catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001"));
```

**4. `GetProductCount_Works` (line 63)** — Doesn't assert the count, AND operates on an empty catalog so it only tests the zero-path.
```csharp
// Fix: add products, then assert count
_catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
_catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-002", "Gadget", 19.99m));
Assert.AreEqual(2, _catalog.GetProductCount());
```

**5. `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` (line 68)** — Applies a 10% discount but never checks any resulting price. A bug in the discount formula (e.g. `Price * fraction` instead of `Price * (1 - fraction)`) would pass.
```csharp
// Fix: assert discounted prices
_catalog.ApplyBulkDiscount(0.10m);
Assert.AreEqual(8.991m, _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001")?.Price);
Assert.AreEqual(17.991m, _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-002")?.Price);
```

**6. `ImportFromCsv_Works` (line 84)** — Imports a row but never verifies it was persisted or parsed correctly.
```csharp
// Fix: assert the imported product
_catalog.ImportFromCsv("SKU-001,Widget,9.99");
var p = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.AreEqual("Widget", p?.Name);
Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, p?.Price);
```

---

## 🟠 High — Weak Assertions (assert exists, not correctness)

